TextEng: The forest is destroying itself all around you and I am trying to find a way to save it.
Text: 숲이 사방에서 스스로를 파괴하고 있어서 구할 방법을 찾고 있어.

TextEng: There are some missing druids that I am seeking and I hoped you might have seen one.
Text: 실종된 드루이드들을 찾고 있는데 혹시 봤을까 해서.

TextEng: Get out of my way you ugly hag, before I chop off your withered head!
Text: 비켜, 이 못생긴 마녀야! 쪼글쪼글한 머리통 날려버리기 전에!

TextEng: Me try to help forest, so it not kill people no more.
Text: 나 숲 도우려고. 숲이 사람 더 안 죽이게.

TextEng: Me just stop in for visit.
You get out of way or me chop you ugly face off.
Text: 비켜 안 그러면 못생긴 얼굴 잘라버려.

TextEng: I was just looking around.
Me need find missing druids to help. You see druid anywhere?
Text: 나 실종된 드루이드 찾아야 해. 드루이드 어디서 봤어?

TextEng: I heard that you were a friend to forest creatures and thought you might know something that could assist me.
Text: 숲 생명체들의 친구라고 들어서 도움 될 만한 걸 알지 않을까 싶었어.

TextEng: I'm just desperate to find some information or anything that could help.
Text: 도움이 될 정보라면 뭐든 필사적으로 찾고 있어.

TextEng: Me thought you friend of animals. Me thought you help, maybe?
Text: 너 동물 친구라 들었어. 너 도와줄 수 있어?

TextEng: Me need help bad. Me take any me can get.
Text: 나 도움 많이 필요해. 뭐든 받을게.

TextEng: I've heard enough. I'll leave now.
Me heard 'nuff. Me go.
I didn't come to gawk. What happened to you?
Text: 구경하러 온 게 아냐. 무슨 일이 있었던 거야?

TextEng: You would certainly fit into the freak show at a circus, but I'm here to find something specific, not to stare.
Text: 서커스 괴물쇼에 딱 맞겠지만 난 구경하러 온 게 아니라 뭔가를 찾으러 왔어.

TextEng: I guess I'll put you out of your misery then hag!
Me not here to stare. What make you ugly?
Text: 나 구경하러 온 거 아냐. 왜 못생겨진 거야?

TextEng: You would win prize for ugliest person, but me look for something, not here for show.
Text: 너 제일 못생긴 사람 상 받겠다. 근데 나 뭐 찾으러 왔어. 구경 아니야.

TextEng: You too ugly to live, so me kill you.
Text: 너무 못생겨서 살면 안 돼. 나 죽일게.

TextEng: What can I do to help you?
What are you willing to give me if I help you?
I don't trust you. I think I'll kill you instead.
Text: 널 믿을 수 없어. 그냥 죽여버리는 게 낫겠어.

TextEng: What me do to help?
What you give me if me help you?
Me no trust you, so me kill you.
Text: 너 못 믿어. 그래서 죽일 거야.

TextEng: All right, what do you want me to do?
That's not enough. I want gold.
What you want me to do?
Not 'nuff. Me want gold.
Okay, I will get this mirror for you.
What will you give me to get this mirror for you?
Okay, me get you mirror.
What you give me if me get you mirror?
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> If you really want my help, you should show some trust by telling me what happened to you.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 정말 도움을 원한다면, 무슨 일이 있었는지 말해서 신뢰를 보여줘.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> You want help, you tell me what happen to you first.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 도움 원하면, 먼저 무슨 일 있었는지 말해.

TextEng: Nothing. Nevermind.
Where did you say the nymph lives again?
I have the mirror right here.
Where you say nymph live?
Me have you mirror here.
Goodbye.
I want the gem and the information though.
Me want gem and information too.
Text: 나 보석이랑 정보 둘 다 원해.

TextEng: Uh... you're right. You are definitely striking to look at.
Text: 어... 네 말이 맞아. 확실히 눈에 띄는 외모야.

TextEng: But you don't look any different.
Uh... you right. Me no think you would look so... lovely.
Text: 어... 네 말 맞아. 이렇게... 예쁠 줄 몰랐어.

TextEng: But you no look no different.
How do I know that you really have any information about them?
Text: 드루이드들에 대해 정말 뭘 알고 있는지 어떻게 믿어?

TextEng: I guess I need any information I can get. What do you need help with?
Text: 정보라면 뭐든 필요해. 뭘 도와주면 돼?

TextEng: How me know you know stuff 'bout druids?
Text: 너 드루이드 진짜 아는 거 어떻게 믿어?

TextEng: Me need help to find them. What me help you with?
Text: 나 그들 찾는 데 도움 필요해. 뭐 도와줘?

TextEng: Why is the druid locked up in your house?
Text: 왜 드루이드가 네 집에 갇혀 있어?

TextEng: Why druid be locked in you house?
Text: 왜 드루이드 네 집에 갇혀 있어?

TextEng: Me look for gem you gots.
I was sent here to collect a gem you have.
If me has to.
That's a distinct possibility.
No, me want you let me have it.
No, I was just hoping to convince you to let me have it.
Text: 아니, 그냥 줬으면 하고 설득하려던 거야.

TextEng: What me do to help?
What can I do to help you?
What you give me if me help you?
What will you give me to get this mirror for you?
You keep yell at me, me bash you like servants.
Text: 계속 나한테 소리 지르면 하인들처럼 때려.

TextEng: If you keep yelling at me like that, I'll show you exactly what I did to your servants.
Text: 계속 그렇게 소리 지르면 네 하인들한테 한 짓 그대로 보여줄게.

TextEng: Me sorry, but you monsters... er, servants, them attack me first.
Text: 미안한데, 네 괴물들... 아, 하인들이 먼저 공격했어.

TextEng: I'm sorry, but your creatures, or servants as you call them, attacked me first.
Text: 미안하지만, 네가 하인이라 부르는 그 생명체들이 먼저 공격했어.
